<br />

<br />
They log tons of stuff... and if you are used to work with tons of logs you know it can be a real hassle to wade through them in order to find what you want.
<br />

<br />
So I suspect it's based upon the GM willingness to take the time and wade through the "evidence" or just notch of another petition and move on to the next one. (So the number of working GM's and the petition queue for the moment probably plays a big part.)
<br />

<br />
Might also be that some GM's are more able to use the search tools better than others, or that only senior GM's might use them? Might be that some players doesn't give the GM the exact time (+TZ)/zone/item/name of toon+npc, and this makes finding the correct info extremely time-consuming.
<br />

<br />
That's why I guess they always had the policy "all trades are final". The logging really isn't there to help people when mistakes are done. It's to catch cheats/sploits/bugs etc. Probably also to catch a GM giving away 100% rez gauntlets to a buddy or something?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
