				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">the sad part about this is that you have to press the trade button to finish the trade. easy fix, do not press the button. confirmation and buttons are there for a reason <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
i see no reason why a gm should give anything back to a player for doing something of their own free will. if they choose to give things back to you, you should count yourself lucky.
<br />

<br />
there is only so much idiot proofing the programmers can do. i am a the senior software developer for my company, and a lot of my job is idiot proofing things that should be obvious.
<br />

<br />
note: i have given things to my pets of value before, and i know that it was my own fault, and make sure not to anymore everytime i go to trade. i understand the frustration of losing something by giving it to your pet, but honestly it is your own fault and you clicked the trade button so you have no one to blame but yourself.
<br />

<br />
wasting GM time on this stuff is sad when there are real problems in the game, like getting stuck in walls and corpse disappearing or stopping cheaters.
<br />

<br />
the only one you should be angry at is yourself, and if you get help or sympathy from anyone, you should count yourself lucky. mistakes made by players should never take up a GM's time. would hate to know that if i have a serious problem, my petition would still be in queue because the GM is busy with someone that shot their own foot off and is irate at everyone and thing besides themselves.
<br />

<br />
i think there should be a rule to make it where a GM should never help those that shoot their own feet off, so they can better help those of us with real problems.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
